A Lively Club

If you like techno music and a cool place to hangout or dance, this is a nice place to explore. A lively crowd, nice decor and atmosphere contribute to it being a highly popular place these days.

The service staff are attentive and vigilant, making it overall a very desirable place to go to for clubbing.

Music is awesome with great lighting! Special shoutout to bartender Javier, he was very patient and fleet footed while dealing with all my special request. Great food from Maha&Co especially with their protein rice bowl.

The night turned out to be quite expensive. The entrance fee alone was $65 without any drinks included. On top of that, two gin and tonics cost about $48. Unfortunately, I didnâ€™t manage to stay long enough for the guest DJ to arrive. The place itself wasnâ€™t as fantastic as expected, especially given the high prices. Ventilation was poor, making it quite uncomfortable inside. Overall, not my favorite place to visit â€” definitely not worth the premium.
Javier was really such a great bartender, love the off the menu cocktails. Super innovative with the drinks and great vibes overall. 10/10 will come back!
